{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GbtjT1fVDTMPvJV8vwxCKg","type":"tool_result","content":"<persisted-output>\nOutput too large (55.8KB). Full output saved to: /Users/apple/.claude/projects/-Users-apple-Code-cogneiss-Products-laravel-starter-kit-inertia-react/13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49/tool-results/toolu_01GbtjT1fVDTMPvJV8vwxCKg.txt\n\nPreview (first 2KB):\n     1→     1→{\n     2→     2→  \"project\": \"Complete Component Library + Per-Org Theme Switcher + Storybook\",\n     3→     3→  \"description\": \"Build a comprehensive, AI-first, maximally-reusable component library covering 100% of Tailux's component vocabulary (and beyond), with a bold per-organization theme switcher that stores each org's visual identity in settings. Uses shadcn registry first, npm packages second, custom code only where needed. Storybook serves as the internal dev catalog. Delivers 4 main deliverables: full component library (150+ typed components), per-org live theme customizer with named presets, SaaS-specific feature components, and Storybook with theme toolbar.\",\n     4→     4→  \"userStories\": [\n     5→     5→    {\n     6→     6→      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n     7→     7→      \"title\": \"Tailux CSS design token foundation\",\n     8→     8→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the Tailux CSS variable system installed so all subsequent components and theme switching work correctly.\",\n     9→     9→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    10→    10→        \"`resources/css/tailux.css` created with `@theme` block containing all custom tokens: `--text-tiny`, `--text-xs-plus`, `--text-sm-plus`, `--shadow-soft`, `--shadow-soft-dark`, `--ease-elastic`, `--color-surface-1/2/3`, `--color-secondary`, `--color-info`, `--color-success`, `--color-warning`, `--color-error`\",\n    11→    11→        \"`resources/css/app.css` contains `@import './tailux.css'`\",\n    12→    12→        \"`resources/css/themes.css` extended with 5 dark theme blocks: `[data-theme-dark=\\\"navy|mirage|mint|black|cinder\\\"]`\",\n    13→    13→        \"`resources/css/themes.css` extended with 6 primary color blocks: `[data-theme-primary=\\\"indigo|blue|green|amber|purple|rose\\\"]`\",\n    14→    14→        \"`resources/css/themes.css` extended with 3 light scheme blocks: `[data-theme-light=\\\"slate|gray|neutral\\\"]`\",\n    15→    15→        \"`npm run build` passes with no errors\",\n...\n</persisted-output>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"c72bffab-0eb3-413c-9706-87d0d1cbe8b9","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/apple/.claude/projects/-Users-apple-Code-cogneiss-Products-laravel-starter-kit-inertia-react/13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49/tool-results/toolu_01AbnARWDUXsGGi3K9wPS3NF.txt","content":"     1→{\n     2→  \"project\": \"Complete Component Library + Per-Org Theme Switcher + Storybook\",\n     3→  \"description\": \"Build a comprehensive, AI-first, maximally-reusable component library covering 100% of Tailux's component vocabulary (and beyond), with a bold per-organization theme switcher that stores each org's visual identity in settings. Uses shadcn registry first, npm packages second, custom code only where needed. Storybook serves as the internal dev catalog. Delivers 4 main deliverables: full component library (150+ typed components), per-org live theme customizer with named presets, SaaS-specific feature components, and Storybook with theme toolbar.\",\n     4→  \"userStories\": [\n     5→    {\n     6→      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n     7→      \"title\": \"Tailux CSS design token foundation\",\n     8→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the Tailux CSS variable system installed so all subsequent components and theme switching work correctly.\",\n     9→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    10→        \"`resources/css/tailux.css` created with `@theme` block containing all custom tokens: `--text-tiny`, `--text-xs-plus`, `--text-sm-plus`, `--shadow-soft`, `--shadow-soft-dark`, `--ease-elastic`, `--color-surface-1/2/3`, `--color-secondary`, `--color-info`, `--color-success`, `--color-warning`, `--color-error`\",\n    11→        \"`resources/css/app.css` contains `@import './tailux.css'`\",\n    12→        \"`resources/css/themes.css` extended with 5 dark theme blocks: `[data-theme-dark=\\\"navy|mirage|mint|black|cinder\\\"]`\",\n    13→        \"`resources/css/themes.css` extended with 6 primary color blocks: `[data-theme-primary=\\\"indigo|blue|green|amber|purple|rose\\\"]`\",\n    14→        \"`resources/css/themes.css` extended with 3 light scheme blocks: `[data-theme-light=\\\"slate|gray|neutral\\\"]`\",\n    15→        \"`npm run build` passes with no errors\",\n    16→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n    17→      ],\n    18→      \"priority\": 1,\n    19→      \"passes\": false,\n    20→      \"inProgress\": true\n    21→    },\n    22→    {\n    23→      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n    24→      \"title\": \"Shared TypeScript theme constants\",\n    25→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need typed constants for all theme options and named presets so components and settings can reference them without magic strings.\",\n    26→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    27→        \"`resources/js/lib/tailux-themes.ts` created with `DARK_THEMES`, `PRIMARY_COLORS`, `LIGHT_THEMES`, `CARD_SKINS`, `RADIUS_OPTIONS` as const arrays with exported types\",\n    28→        \"`THEME_PRESETS` array defined in the same file, each preset having a name (e.g. `\\\"Corporate\\\"`, `\\\"Midnight\\\"`, `\\\"Sunset\\\"`, `\\\"Forest\\\"`, `\\\"Ocean\\\"`, `\\\"Candy\\\"`) and values for all 5 theme dimensions\",\n    29→        \"`resources/js/lib/color-variants.ts` created with `colorVariants` CVA definitions for `filled`, `soft`, `outlined` variants across 7 semantic colors (primary, secondary, info, success, warning, error, neutral)\",\n    30→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n    31→      ],\n    32→      \"priority\": 2,\n    33→      \"passes\": false\n    34→    },\n    35→    {\n    36→      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n    37→      \"title\": \"ThemeSettings backend — add Tailux theme fields\",\n    38→      \"description\": \"As an admin, I need the system to store the org's dark theme, primary color, light scheme, card skin, and border radius in the database so visual identity persists.\",\n    39→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    40→        \"`app/Settings/ThemeSettings.php` extended with 5 new public fields: `dark_color_scheme` (default: `'navy'`), `primary_color` (default: `'indigo'`), `light_color_scheme` (default: `'slate'`), `card_skin` (default: `'shadow'`), `border_radius` (default: `'default'`)\",\n    41→        \"New settings migration created in `database/settings/` for the 5 new fields\",\n    42→        \"`php artisan migrate` completes successfully\",\n    43→        \"`SettingsOverlayServiceProvider::OVERLAY_MAP` updated with theme field mappings, `orgOverridable: true`\",\n    44→        \"`php artisan settings:cache` completes successfully\",\n    45→        \"`vendor/bin/pint --dirty --format agent` passes\"\n    46→      ],\n    47→      \"priority\": 3,\n    48→      \"passes\": false\n    49→    },\n    50→    {\n    51→      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n    52→      \"title\": \"System setting — allow users to customize their own theme\",\n    53→      \"description\": \"As a system admin, I want a global toggle \\\"Allow users to customize their own theme\\\" so I can decide whether regular (non-admin) users in any organization can use the theme customizer to change their personal theme preferences.\",\n    54→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    55→        \"A new boolean field `allow_user_theme_customization` (default: `false`) added to an appropriate existing Settings class (e.g. `GeneralSettings`) or a new class if none fits\",\n    56→        \"A new settings migration in `database/settings/` adds the field\",\n    57→        \"`php artisan migrate` completes successfully\",\n    58→        \"The field is NOT `orgOverridable` — it is a system-wide toggle only the system admin controls\",\n    59→        \"A Filament settings page exposes this as a labeled toggle: \\\"Allow users to customize their own theme\\\" with helper text: \\\"When enabled, all authenticated users can use the theme customizer. When disabled, only organization admins can.\\\"\",\n    60→        \"`php artisan settings:cache` completes successfully\",\n    61→        \"`vendor/bin/pint --dirty --format agent` passes\"\n    62→      ],\n    63→      \"priority\": 4,\n    64→      \"passes\": false\n    65→    },\n    66→    {\n    67→      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n    68→      \"title\": \"Share theme data and permissions via Inertia\",\n    69→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the current org's theme settings, the user's personal mode preference, and customization permissions all passed to the frontend on every page load.\",\n    70→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    71→        \"`app/Http/Middleware/HandleInertiaRequests.php` `share()` method includes a `'theme'` key with: `dark`, `primary`, `light`, `skin`, `radius` (from `ThemeSettings`); `canCustomize` boolean — `true` if current user is an org admin OR `allow_user_theme_customization` is `true`; `userMode` — the authenticated user's personal preference (`'dark'`, `'light'`, or `'system'`, default `'system'`) read from `user_preferences` or a users table column\",\n    72→        \"Frontend `usePage().props.theme` is typed correctly in the project's types file\",\n    73→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\",\n    74→        \"`vendor/bin/pint --dirty --format agent` passes\"\n    75→      ],\n    76→      \"priority\": 5,\n    77→      \"passes\": false\n    78→    },\n    79→    {\n    80→      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n    81→      \"title\": \"Per-user dark/light/system mode preference\",\n    82→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to choose whether the app uses dark mode, light mode, or follows my operating system preference, independently of the org's chosen color palette.\",\n    83→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    84→        \"Users table (or a `user_preferences` table) gains a `theme_mode` column: `'dark' | 'light' | 'system'` (default `'system'`)\",\n    85→        \"Migration created and `php artisan migrate` passes\",\n    86→        \"A mode toggle component (`resources/js/components/ui/mode-toggle.tsx`) renders 3 options: Dark / Light / System (with OS icon), placed in the existing user settings or app header\",\n    87→        \"Selecting a mode: (1) immediately applies `.dark` class or removes it from `document.documentElement` based on selection; (2) persists the choice via PATCH to a `/user/preferences` route; (3) choice survives page reload\",\n    88→        \"\\\"System\\\" mode respects `prefers-color-scheme` via a `matchMedia` listener that updates the class reactively if the OS preference changes\",\n    89→        \"`vendor/bin/pint --dirty --format agent` passes\",\n    90→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n    91→      ],\n    92→      \"priority\": 6,\n    93→      \"passes\": false\n    94→    },\n    95→    {\n    96→      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n    97→      \"title\": \"Apply Tailux theme attributes on page load\",\n    98→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want the page to load with my organization's correct dark theme, primary color, card skin, and my personal mode preference already applied so there is no flash of incorrect styling.\",\n    99→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   100→        \"`resources/js/components/theme-from-props.tsx` extended to set `data-theme-dark`, `data-theme-primary`, `data-theme-light`, `data-card-skin`, `data-radius` on `document.documentElement` from `usePage().props.theme`\",\n   101→        \"`theme-from-props.tsx` also applies user mode on mount: if `userMode = 'dark'` → add `.dark`; if `userMode = 'light'` → remove `.dark`; if `userMode = 'system'` → apply based on `matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)')`\",\n   102→        \"Existing `data-theme`, `data-radius`, `data-font` behavior is unchanged (backward-compatible)\",\n   103→        \"Setting `dark_color_scheme = 'cinder'` in DB → page loads with Cinder palette applied\",\n   104→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n   105→      ],\n   106→      \"priority\": 7,\n   107→      \"passes\": false\n   108→    },\n   109→    {\n   110→      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n   111→      \"title\": \"Storybook setup with Tailux theme toolbar\",\n   112→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need Storybook running with a theme toolbar so I can visually catalog and test every component across all theme combinations without running the Laravel backend.\",\n   113→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   114→        \"Storybook devDependencies installed: `storybook`, `@storybook/react-vite`, `@storybook/addon-docs`, `@storybook/addon-themes`, `@storybook/addon-a11y`, `@storybook/blocks`\",\n   115→        \"`.storybook/main.ts` created; stories glob points to `resources/js/stories/**/*.stories.@(ts|tsx)`; framework is `@storybook/react-vite`\",\n   116→        \"`.storybook/preview.tsx` created with: mock stubs for `usePage`, `Link`, `router`, `useForm` from `@inertiajs/react`; toolbar globals for `darkMode`, `darkTheme`, `primaryColor`, `lightTheme`, `cardSkin`, `radius` that apply corresponding data attributes\",\n   117→        \"`npm run storybook` starts on port 6006 with no errors, without requiring Laravel to be running\",\n   118→        \"All 5 dark themes, all 6 primary colors, and dark/light/system mode switch via toolbar\",\n   119→        \"`npm run build` does not include Storybook in production bundle\"\n   120→      ],\n   121→      \"priority\": 8,\n   122→      \"passes\": false\n   123→    },\n   124→    {\n   125→      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n   126→      \"title\": \"Theme Customizer component with presets\",\n   127→      \"description\": \"As an admin (or permitted user), I want a floating theme panel where I can apply a named preset in one click or fine-tune individual dimensions, then save for the organization.\",\n   128→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   129→        \"`resources/js/components/ui/theme-customizer.tsx` created as a fixed-position floating panel (right side of screen)\",\n   130→        \"The floating button is only rendered when `usePage().props.theme.canCustomize` is `true`\",\n   131→        \"Panel has a \\\"Presets\\\" section at the top showing named preset cards (e.g. Corporate, Midnight, Sunset, Forest, Ocean, Candy); clicking a preset applies all 5 dimensions at once\",\n   132→        \"Panel also has individual sections for: 5 dark theme swatches; 6 primary color diamonds; 3 light scheme previews; 2 card skin options; 6 border radius options\",\n   133→        \"Selecting any option immediately updates the corresponding `data-*` attribute on `document.documentElement` (optimistic UI, no page reload)\",\n   134→        \"\\\"Save for Organization\\\" button POSTs the current selections to the settings API and shows a success toast\",\n   135→        \"\\\"Reset to defaults\\\" link reverts all attributes and clears saved org overrides\",\n   136→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n   137→      ],\n   138→      \"priority\": 9,\n   139→      \"passes\": false\n   140→    },\n   141→    {\n   142→      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n   143→      \"title\": \"Embed ThemeCustomizer in branding settings page\",\n   144→      \"description\": \"As an admin, I want the theme customizer available inline on the branding settings page alongside a live dashboard mockup preview.\",\n   145→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   146→        \"`resources/js/pages/settings/branding.tsx` updated to embed `ThemeCustomizer` as an inline panel (not floating)\",\n   147→        \"Existing branding fields remain unchanged and functional\",\n   148→        \"Theme changes apply the same live previ