{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ds2fMjXAmJbY5YfnkQ9UFW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Tailux CSS Design Token Foundation\n     3→ * Extends the base shadcn/Tailwind theme with Tailux-specific tokens.\n     4→ * Imported by app.css before the main @theme block.\n     5→ */\n     6→\n     7→@theme {\n     8→    /* Extended text size tokens */\n     9→    --text-tiny: 0.625rem; /* 10px */\n    10→    --text-xs-plus: 0.8125rem; /* 13px — between xs (12px) and sm (14px) */\n    11→    --text-sm-plus: 0.9375rem; /* 15px — between sm (14px) and base (16px) */\n    12→\n    13→    /* Shadow tokens */\n    14→    --shadow-soft: 0 1px 3px 0 oklch(0 0 0 / 0.08), 0 1px 2px -1px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.06);\n    15→    --shadow-soft-dark: 0 1px 3px 0 oklch(0 0 0 / 0.3), 0 1px 2px -1px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.2);\n    16→\n    17→    /* Easing token */\n    18→    --ease-elastic: cubic-bezier(0.68, -0.55, 0.265, 1.55);\n    19→\n    20→    /* Surface color tokens (neutral layered backgrounds) */\n    21→    --color-surface-1: var(--surface-1);\n    22→    --color-surface-2: var(--surface-2);\n    23→    --color-surface-3: var(--surface-3);\n    24→\n    25→    /* Semantic status color tokens */\n    26→    --color-secondary: var(--tailux-secondary);\n    27→    --color-info: var(--tailux-info);\n    28→    --color-success: var(--tailux-success);\n    29→    --color-warning: var(--tailux-warning);\n    30→    --color-error: var(--tailux-error);\n    31→}\n    32→\n    33→/* Surface and semantic color raw values — light mode */\n    34→:root {\n    35→    --surface-1: oklch(0.985 0 0);\n    36→    --surface-2: oklch(0.97 0 0);\n    37→    --surface-3: oklch(0.94 0 0);\n    38→\n    39→    --tailux-secondary: oklch(0.5 0.12 255);\n    40→    --tailux-info: oklch(0.5 0.16 240);\n    41→    --tailux-success: oklch(0.5 0.16 145);\n    42→    --tailux-warning: oklch(0.6 0.18 75);\n    43→    --tailux-error: oklch(0.52 0.22 27);\n    44→}\n    45→\n    46→/* Surface and semantic color raw values — dark mode */\n    47→.dark {\n    48→    --surface-1: oklch(0.18 0 0);\n    49→    --surface-2: oklch(0.22 0 0);\n    50→    --surface-3: oklch(0.26 0 0);\n    51→\n    52→    --tailux-secondary: oklch(0.68 0.1 255);\n    53→    --tailux-info: oklch(0.68 0.14 240);\n    54→    --tailux-success: oklch(0.68 0.14 145);\n    55→    --tailux-warning: oklch(0.78 0.16 75);\n    56→    --tailux-error: oklch(0.68 0.2 27);\n    57→}\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"5ea35ec5-7782-48ce-b95b-fce9a563aed0","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/apple/Code/cogneiss/Products/laravel-starter-kit-inertia-react/resources/css/tailux.css","content":"/*\n * Tailux CSS Design Token Foundation\n * Extends the base shadcn/Tailwind theme with Tailux-specific tokens.\n * Imported by app.css before the main @theme block.\n */\n\n@theme {\n    /* Extended text size tokens */\n    --text-tiny: 0.625rem; /* 10px */\n    --text-xs-plus: 0.8125rem; /* 13px — between xs (12px) and sm (14px) */\n    --text-sm-plus: 0.9375rem; /* 15px — between sm (14px) and base (16px) */\n\n    /* Shadow tokens */\n    --shadow-soft: 0 1px 3px 0 oklch(0 0 0 / 0.08), 0 1px 2px -1px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.06);\n    --shadow-soft-dark: 0 1px 3px 0 oklch(0 0 0 / 0.3), 0 1px 2px -1px oklch(0 0 0 / 0.2);\n\n    /* Easing token */\n    --ease-elastic: cubic-bezier(0.68, -0.55, 0.265, 1.55);\n\n    /* Surface color tokens (neutral layered backgrounds) */\n    --color-surface-1: var(--surface-1);\n    --color-surface-2: var(--surface-2);\n    --color-surface-3: var(--surface-3);\n\n    /* Semantic status color tokens */\n    --color-secondary: var(--tailux-secondary);\n    --color-info: var(--tailux-info);\n    --color-success: var(--tailux-success);\n    --color-warning: var(--tailux-warning);\n    --color-error: var(--tailux-error);\n}\n\n/* Surface and semantic color raw values — light mode */\n:root {\n    --surface-1: oklch(0.985 0 0);\n    --surface-2: oklch(0.97 0 0);\n    --surface-3: oklch(0.94 0 0);\n\n    --tailux-secondary: oklch(0.5 0.12 255);\n    --tailux-info: oklch(0.5 0.16 240);\n    --tailux-success: oklch(0.5 0.16 145);\n    --tailux-warning: oklch(0.6 0.18 75);\n    --tailux-error: oklch(0.52 0.22 27);\n}\n\n/* Surface and semantic color raw values — dark mode */\n.dark {\n    --surface-1: oklch(0.18 0 0);\n    --surface-2: oklch(0.22 0 0);\n    --surface-3: oklch(0.26 0 0);\n\n    --tailux-secondary: oklch(0.68 0.1 255);\n    --tailux-info: oklch(0.68 0.14 240);\n    --tailux-success: oklch(0.68 0.14 145);\n    --tailux-warning: oklch(0.78 0.16 75);\n    --tailux-error: oklch(0.68 0.2 27);\n}\n","numLines":58,"startLine":1,"totalLines":58}}}
