{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MPpTwbbX7WgC92xgBw3tHh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see a big problem here! The wayfinder vite plugin is calling `php85` in a loop, accumulating more and more `-d memory_limit=512M` flags. This is a bug in vite.config.ts. The `command` option in the wayfinder plugin seems to be getting executed repeatedly.\n\nLet me look at what's happening. In the `vite.config.ts`, the wayfinder plugin has:\n```js\ncommand: \"'/Users/apple/Library/Application Support/Herd/bin/php85' -d memory_limit=512M artisan wayfinder:generate\"\n\n\n```\n\nBut it seems there's a vite rebuild loop happening and each vite build spawns a new wayfinder:generate process. This is causing runaway processes.\n\nThe first thing I should do is kill these hanging processes. Then I need to figure out the correct way to run the build. Actually, looking at the process output, it seems the php85 command has accumulated hundreds of `-d memory_limit=512M` flags, which means there's a recursive invocation happening—likely because vite watch is triggering the wayfinder:generate command when wayfinder itself modifies files, creating a feedback loop.\n\nFor a production build this shouldn't occur unless the wayfinder plugin configuration is misconfigured. Looking at the actual command, I'm seeing repeated flags stacked on top of each other, which suggests the shell script is re-invoking itself—this appears to be a pre-existing bug in the vite config. I need to kill these processes first and then try a different build approach.\n\n```","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2143,"cache_read_input_tokens":77486,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2143},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"se