{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FywmVD4BjXt4j8ezcAsLej","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the vite.config.ts issue. The wayfinder plugin is calling php85 in a way that creates a loop. The problem seems to be that the `command` in vite.config uses an absolute path with quotes, but when it's run as a bash script, it might be treating `php85` as a bash script that invokes itself.\n\nWait, looking at the path: `/Users/apple/Library/Application Support/Herd/bin/php85`. This is probably a shell script that calls the actual PHP binary. When the vite wayfinder plugin calls this, and this script is invoked via bash, it might be calling itself recursively.\n\n\nThe issue is that the command string has extra quotes around the php85 path, which could be causing the shell to interpret it incorrectly when Node.js executes it. I should try using the actual PHP binary directly instead of going through Herd's wrapper script, or at least remove the unnecessary quoting to let the shell parse it properly.\n\nLooking at the vite config more carefully, I notice the wayfinder command is accumulating hundreds of `-d memory_limit=512M` flags on each invocation. This suggests the command itself is being appended to repeatedly rather than executed cleanly. I think what's happening is that Vite detects the generated routes file changing after the wayfinder plugin runs, which triggers a rebuild, which runs the command again, creating a feedback loop where the command string keeps growing.\n\nBut actually, looking at the timestamps of the PHP processes (12:27AM through 12:57AM), these are remnants from my earlier failed build attempts. When I killed the vite processes, the spawned PHP child processes weren't cleaned up properly and are still running in the background. I need to kill all those lingering PHP processes first, then manually generate the wayfinder routes and run a clean build.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":124,"cache_read_input_tokens":80508,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":124},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"50a34eea-bd61-49dd-873a-0176b9cdb933"}
