that more carefully with proper typing rather than a direct cast. intermediate cast - `usePage().props as unknown as SharedProps` or just ignore with `// eslint-disable-next-line`.\n\n   Actually, looking at it more carefully - TypeScript says \"Conversion of type 'PageProps & ...' to type 'SharedProps' may be a mistake because neither type sufficiently overlaps.\" The `SharedProps` interface only has `honeypot`, but the full page props have more. The issue is that `SharedProps` doesn't extend the base page props type. Fix: use `(usePage().props as unknown as SharedProps)` to do a double cast.\n\n9. **`puck-blocks/data-list-block.tsx(28,32)`: Type mismatch in Array.map callback**\n   The issue is that `items` is typed as `unknown[]`, so I can't annotate the callback parameter as `Record<string, unknown>` directly. The simpler fix is to change the prop definition from `data?: unknown[]` to `data?: Record<string, unknown>[]` so the array elements are properly typed from the start.\n\n10. **`puck-blocks/data-list-block.tsx(38,29)`: Type 'unknown' is not assignable to type 'ReactNode'**\n    `{String(item.email)}` - wait\n\n, this is wrapped in String(), so it should be string. Let me re-read. Oh wait, the error is at line 38: `{item.email && (<span>...{String(item.email)}</span>)}`. The `item.email` is `unknown`, and `unknown && JSX.Element` gives `unknown | JSX.Element = unknown` which is not ReactNode. Fix: check `item.email !== undefined && item.email !== null && (...)` or change the condition to `{typeof item.email === 'string' && (...)}`.\n\n11. **`ui/calendar.tsx(189,9)`: Type mismatch for ChevronIcon**\n    The orientation type includes `\"up\"` but the component doesn't accept `\"up\"`. This is a react-day-picker/lucide-react type version mismatch. Fix: might need an intermediate cast or just ignore with eslint-disable.\n\nFor the `item.email` issue, I need to be more careful about how TypeScript handles logical AND with unknown types - the condition needs to narrow the type properly before using it in JSX.\n\n12. **`echo.ts(16,16)`: Generic type 'Echo<T>' requires 1 type argument(s)**\n    `interface Window { Echo?: Echo; }` - Echo needs a type parameter. Fix: `Echo?: Echo<any>` or `Echo?: InstanceType<typeof EchoClass>`.\n\n13. **`puck-config.tsx` - JSX namespace issues**\n    The errors are about `JSX.IntrinsicElements` not found as namespace and puck components. These look like complex type issues.\n\n14. **`pages/pages/edit.tsx`** - useForm type issues - the form was created without proper typing, so form.data, form.errors etc are all typed as `unknown`. Fix: properly type the useForm call.\n\n15. **`pages/pages/show.tsx`** - puck data type issues to resolve.\n\n16. **`contact/create.tsx`** - The flash object is typed as an empty object, so accessing `flash?.status` fails. I need to add the flash property to SharedData or cast it properly.\n\n17. **`terms/accept.tsx`** - The Form component is receiving an object with number and string values, but it expects all string values. Also, the Button component doesn't support a render function as children, which is causing type errors.\n\nI'm starting to see the pattern here—many of these are type definition issues where interfaces aren't properly aligned with how they're being used.\n\nNow I'm going to work through each one with targeted fixes. For the dynamic module loading, I'll cast it to the right component type. For the avatar properties, I'll use optional chaining with undefined fallbacks. The command dialog needs several fixes around keyboard shortcuts and route method calls. The data table needs the preserveState prop removed, and the honeypot fields need a double cast to work around the type system. The puck blocks need proper callback typing, and the calendar needs a type cast as well.\n\nMoving on to the remaining files—I need to add a generic parameter to the echo utility, fix JSX issues in the puck config, type the form hook properly in the pages edit view, correct the puck data type in the show view, handle the flash type in the contact creation, and fix the form data type and button render prop in the terms acceptance.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3494,"cache_read_input_tokens":123126,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3494},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"6a95b2e1-cde9-4a20-ab5a-811791238bd4"}
