{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018jZF4gb8BdWDJPgQD1Z9PG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import PageController from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PageController';\n     2→import AppLayout from '@/layouts/app-layout';\n     3→import { dashboard } from '@/routes';\n     4→import { type BreadcrumbItem } from '@/types';\n     5→import { Head, useForm } from '@inertiajs/react';\n     6→import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';\n     7→\n     8→import InputError from '@/components/input-error';\n     9→import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';\n    10→import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';\n    11→import { Label } from '@/components/ui/label';\n    12→import {\n    13→    Select,\n    14→    SelectContent,\n    15→    SelectItem,\n    16→    SelectTrigger,\n    17→    SelectValue,\n    18→} from '@/components/ui/select';\n    19→import { Switch } from '@/components/ui/switch';\n    20→import { puckConfig } from '@/lib/puck-config';\n    21→\n    22→const PuckEditor = lazy(() =>\n    23→    import('@measured/puck').then((m) => {\n    24→        void import('@measured/puck/puck.css');\n    25→        return { default: m.Puck };\n    26→    }),\n    27→);\n    28→\n    29→interface PageRecord {\n    30→    id: number;\n    31→    name: string;\n    32→    slug: string;\n    33→    puck_json: Record<string, unknown>;\n    34→    is_published: boolean;\n    35→    meta_description?: string | null;\n    36→    meta_image?: string | null;\n    37→}\n    38→\n    39→interface TemplateOption {\n    40→    key: string;\n    41→    label: string;\n    42→    data: { root: Record<string, unknown>; content: unknown[] };\n    43→}\n    44→\n    45→interface Props {\n    46→    page: PageRecord | null;\n    47→    puckJson: { root: Record<string, unknown>; content: unknown[] };\n    48→    templates?: TemplateOption[];\n    49→}\n    50→\n    51→const emptyPuckData = { root: {}, content: [] };\n    52→\n    53→export default function PageEdit({ page, puckJson, templates = [] }: Props) {\n    54→    const isCreate = page === null;\n    55→    const initialData = puckJson?.content ? puckJson : emptyPuckData;\n    56→\n    57→    const { data, setData, post, put, processing, errors } = useForm({\n    58→        name: page?.name ?? '',\n    59→        slug: page?.slug ?? '',\n    60→        puck_json: initialData as {\n    61→            root: Record<string, unknown>;\n    62→            content: unknown[];\n    63→        },\n    64→        is_published: page?.is_published ?? false,\n    65→        meta_description: page?.meta_description ?? '',\n    66→        meta_image: page?.meta_image ?? '',\n    67→    });\n    68→\n    69→    const breadcrumbs: BreadcrumbItem[] = [\n    70→        { title: 'Dashboard', href: dashboard().url },\n    71→        { title: 'Pages', href: PageController.index().url },\n    72→        {\n    73→            title: isCreate ? 'New page' : (page?.name ?? 'Edit'),\n    74→            href: isCreate\n    75→                ? PageController.create().url\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"704e1148-a963-4ef2-809e-c004d829ea4b","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/apple/Code/cogneiss/Products/laravel-starter-kit-inertia-react/resources/js/pages/pages/edit.tsx","content":"import PageController from '@/actions/App/Http/Controllers/PageController';\nimport AppLayout from '@/layouts/app-layout';\nimport { dashboard } from '@/routes';\nimport { type BreadcrumbItem } from '@/types';\nimport { Head, useForm } from '@inertiajs/react';\nimport { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';\n\nimport InputError from '@/components/input-error';\nimport { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';\nimport { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';\nimport { Label } from '@/components/ui/label';\nimport {\n    Select,\n    SelectContent,\n    SelectItem,\n    SelectTrigger,\n    SelectValue,\n} from '@/components/ui/select';\nimport { Switch } from '@/components/ui/switch';\nimport { puckConfig } from '@/lib/puck-config';\n\nconst PuckEditor = lazy(() =>\n    import('@measured/puck').then((m) => {\n        void import('@measured/puck/puck.css');\n        return { default: m.Puck };\n    }),\n);\n\ninterface PageRecord {\n    id: number;\n    name: string;\n    slug: string;\n    puck_json: Record<string, unknown>;\n    is_published: boolean;\n    meta_description?: string | null;\n    meta_image?: string | null;\n}\n\ninterface TemplateOption {\n    key: string;\n    label: string;\n    data: { root: Record<string, unknown>; content: unknown[] };\n}\n\ninterface Props {\n    page: PageRecord | null;\n    puckJson: { root: Record<string, unknown>; content: unknown[] };\n    templates?: TemplateOption[];\n}\n\nconst emptyPuckData = { root: {}, content: [] };\n\nexport default function PageEdit({ page, puckJson, templates = [] }: Props) {\n    const isCreate = page === null;\n    const initialData = puckJson?.content ? puckJson : emptyPuckData;\n\n    const { data, setData, post, put, processing, errors } = useForm({\n        name: page?.name ?? '',\n        slug: page?.slug ?? '',\n        puck_json: initialData as {\n            root: Record<string, unknown>;\n            content: unknown[];\n        },\n        is_published: page?.is_published ?? false,\n        meta_description: page?.meta_description ?? '',\n        meta_image: page?.meta_image ?? '',\n    });\n\n    const breadcrumbs: BreadcrumbItem[] = [\n        { title: 'Dashboard', href: dashboard().url },\n        { title: 'Pages', href: PageController.index().url },\n        {\n            title: isCreate ? 'New page' : (page?.name ?? 'Edit'),\n            href: isCreate\n                ? PageController.create().url","numLines":75,"startLine":1,"totalLines":246}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JHoSj5tEMzPVx963rEHety","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough context to fix the TypeScript errors. Let me make the fixes:\n\n1. **`app.tsx(24)`**: Cast module properly\n2. **`app-header.tsx(259)` and `user-info.tsx(17)`**: `null` coercion for avatar\n3. **`command-dialog.tsx`**: \n   - Line 156: Cast 'Mod+k' as RegisterableHotkey type\n   - Line 313: Remove `.url()` fallback, just use `.url`\n   - Line 329: `run(editUserProfile().url)`  \n   - Line 336: `run(logoutUrl.url, true)` and fix line 230 as well\n4. **`data-table.tsx(1065)`**: Remove `preserveState: true`\n5. **`honeypot-fields.tsx(20)`**: Use `as unknown as SharedProps`\n6. **`puck-blocks/data-list-block.tsx`**: Fix map callback types\n7. **`calendar.tsx(189)`**: Type cast ChevronIcon\n8. **`echo.ts(16)`**: Add `<unknown>` to Echo generic\n9. **`puck-config.tsx`**: Still working through remaining fixes...\n\nNow looking at the pages/edit.tsx issue more carefully. The problem is that Inertia v2's useForm has stricter typing and won't accept nested unknown values in the puck_json field. The type error suggests FormDataType doesn't allow Record<string, unknown> nested inside the form data structure, so I need to find a way to properly type this complex nested object without relying on unknown arrays.\n\nFor pages/show.tsx, the puck_json data coming from props has the same structure but needs to match what the Puck component expects. And in terms/accept.tsx, the form data object needs to align with what the Form component's data prop is typed to receive.\n\nI'm realizing these are all variations of the same Inertia Form v2 typing constraint issue—the form data needs to be simple key-value pairs, not nested objects with arrays. Rather than refactoring the logic, I should use targeted type assertions to work around these strict type checks. Let me also check the app-header.tsx structure to see if there are similar issues there, then move on to understanding the flash.status problem in contact/create.tsx.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2346,"cache_read_input_tokens":130946,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2346},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"e67f6078-dd9c-455d-9a49-e3000b36dc71"}
