{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S9hdZyJ458m1bZj4GbU3qp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Laravel Echo bootstrap for Reverb (Pusher protocol).\n     3→ * Import this in app.tsx when using real-time broadcasting, e.g.:\n     4→ *\n     5→ *   import './echo';\n     6→ *\n     7→ * Then use window.Echo in components to listen to private/user channels.\n     8→ * Requires BROADCAST_CONNECTION=reverb and VITE_REVERB_* env vars.\n     9→ */\n    10→\n    11→import Echo from 'laravel-echo';\n    12→import Pusher from 'pusher-js';\n    13→\n    14→declare global {\n    15→    interface Window {\n    16→        Echo?: Echo;\n    17→        Pusher?: typeof Pusher;\n    18→    }\n    19→}\n    20→\n    21→const key = import.meta.env.VITE_REVERB_APP_KEY;\n    22→const host = import.meta.env.VITE_REVERB_HOST ?? 'localhost';\n    23→const port = import.meta.env.VITE_REVERB_PORT ?? '8080';\n    24→const scheme = import.meta.env.VITE_REVERB_SCHEME ?? 'http';\n    25→\n    26→if (key) {\n    27→    window.Pusher = Pusher;\n    28→\n    29→    window.Echo = new Echo({\n    30→        broadcaster: 'reverb',\n    31→        key,\n    32→        wsHost: host,\n    33→        wsPort: port,\n    34→        wssPort: port,\n    35→        forceTLS: scheme === 'https',\n    36→        enabledTransports: ['ws', 'wss'],\n    37→    });\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"a18b0978-3e74-4cd5-9260-6efbded7a4b7","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/apple/Code/cogneiss/Products/laravel-starter-kit-inertia-react/resources/js/echo.ts","content":"/**\n * Laravel Echo bootstrap for Reverb (Pusher protocol).\n * Import this in app.tsx when using real-time broadcasting, e.g.:\n *\n *   import './echo';\n *\n * Then use window.Echo in components to listen to private/user channels.\n * Requires BROADCAST_CONNECTION=reverb and VITE_REVERB_* env vars.\n */\n\nimport Echo from 'laravel-echo';\nimport Pusher from 'pusher-js';\n\ndeclare global {\n    interface Window {\n        Echo?: Echo;\n        Pusher?: typeof Pusher;\n    }\n}\n\nconst key = import.meta.env.VITE_REVERB_APP_KEY;\nconst host = import.meta.env.VITE_REVERB_HOST ?? 'localhost';\nconst port = import.meta.env.VITE_REVERB_PORT ?? '8080';\nconst scheme = import.meta.env.VITE_REVERB_SCHEME ?? 'http';\n\nif (key) {\n    window.Pusher = Pusher;\n\n    window.Echo = new Echo({\n        broadcaster: 'reverb',\n        key,\n        wsHost: host,\n        wsPort: port,\n        wssPort: port,\n        forceTLS: scheme === 'https',\n        enabledTransports: ['ws', 'wss'],\n    });\n}\n","numLines":39,"startLine":1,"totalLines":39}}}
