{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GorqGWbsCixfQkNCT14wTR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, for line 313, I need to re-read that section. The error is:\n`resources/js/components/command-dialog.tsx(313,71): error TS2349: This expression is not callable. Type 'never' has no call signatures.`\n\nLine 313 is: `(item.href.url ?? item.href.url())`\n\nThis is `item.href.url ?? item.href.url()`. The `??` (nullish coalescing) means \"if `.url` is null or undefined, call `.url()` instead\". But since `.url` is already a string (truthy, non-null), the right side is `never` according to TypeScript. \n\nThe issue is that TypeScript narrows the type after the `??` check — if `item.href.url` is a string, then it can't also be callable, so the right side becomes unreachable. I need to check what `InertiaLinkProps['href']` actually is to understand whether `.url` can be both a string property and a method.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":320,"cache_read_input_tokens":145799,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":320},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"151f5f2c-a6d2-408f-8c62-2999cafa53bb"}
