{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01M8tU3BaLPEEisgrpR9VEYH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `useForm` in Inertia v2 has strict typing. The issue is that `content: unknown[]` doesn't satisfy the `FormDataType` constraint. The `FormDataType` expects values to be `FormDataConvertible`, and `unknown[]` doesn't satisfy that constraint.\n\nFix: Change `content: unknown[]` to `content: Record<string, unknown>[]` in the type assertion, since we changed DataListBlockProps earlier. Or alternatively, cast `puck_json` to `any` in the useForm.\n\nActually, the simplest fix: change the `content` type from `unknown[]` to `Record<string, unknown>[]` throughout this file. \n\nI need to apply the same fix to both the edit and show pages. The `content` field needs to be typed as `Record<string, unknown>[]` instead of `unknown[]` in the interfaces, and then update the `useForm` initialization to match. Let me make these changes across both files.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1082,"cache_read_input_tokens":157504,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1082},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"a46e015d-dbec-4a3f-bc27-684198cf9a1e"}
