{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014me3mNKzTnYJB5vPcV8P5U","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"For the `data` prop on Form: The error says `data` prop expects `string`. This is because `Form` is an HTML `<form>` element wrapper, and in HTML/React, the `data` attribute on `<form>` would be a string (like `data-foo=\"bar\"`). But there's no standard `data` attribute for forms - it would be a custom `data-*` attribute.\n\nLooking at the Inertia v2 Form component, the `data` prop might be used as form submission data, but its TypeScript type might be expecting just standard HTML attributes.\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully: `TermsAcceptController.store.form()` returns the form action/method props. \n\nThe `data` prop here is trying to pass custom data to the form, but since `Form` extends `React.FormHTMLAttributes`, it doesn't accept object-type data props. The form data is already being submitted through hidden input fields, so I can just remove the `data` prop entirely.\n\nNow looking at the Button render prop, I'm examining how the button is structured with its submit type and disabled state.\n\nThe Button component doesn't actually support render props, and there's no `processing` state available from this HTML-based form approach anyway. I should replace the render prop pattern with a simple static label instead.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":400,"cache_read_input_tokens":161931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":400},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"e92ffbbd-f711-469e-a7c7-97eaa1083f21"}
