{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019KVHr9NNi9cfGeGH9Yg8MS","type":"tool_result","content":"#!/bin/sh\n#\n# Pre-commit hook: Pint (PHP style), model/seeder and docs checks.\n# Install: cp scripts/pre-commit .git/hooks/pre-commit && chmod +x .git/hooks/pre-commit\n#\n\nset -e\nROOT=\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\n# 1. Laravel Pint (PHP code style)\necho \"📝 Running Pint...\"\nif ! vendor/bin/pint --test --dirty 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"❌ Pint check failed. Run: vendor/bin/pint --dirty --format agent\"\n    exit 1\nfi\necho \"✅ Pint passed\"\n\n# 3. New models: seeders and specs (exclude Concerns/ traits, Scopes/, and known non-models)\nSTAGED_MODELS=$(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=A | grep -E '^app/Models/.*\\.php$' | grep -v -E '^app/Models/(Concerns|Scopes)/' || true)\nSKIP_NAMES=\"BelongsToOrganization OrganizationScope Categorizable TermsVersion UserTermsAcceptance\"\n\nif [ -n \"$STAGED_MODELS\" ]; then\n    MISSING_SEEDERS=\"\"\n    MISSING_SPECS=\"\"\n    for MODEL_FILE in $STAGED_MODELS; do\n        MODEL_NAME=$(basename \"$MODEL_FILE\" .php)\n        case \" $SKIP_NAMES \" in *\" $MODEL_NAME \"*) continue ;; esac\n        SEEDER_FOUND=false\n        for CATEGORY in essential development production; do\n            if [ -f \"database/seeders/$CATEGORY/${MODEL_NAME}Seeder.php\" ]; then\n                SEEDER_FOUND=true\n                break\n            fi\n        done\n        if [ \"$SEEDER_FOUND\" = false ]; then\n            MISSING_SEEDERS=\"${MISSING_SEEDERS}${MISSING_SEEDERS:+, }$MODEL_NAME\"\n        fi\n        if [ ! -f \"database/seeders/specs/${MODEL_NAME}.json\" ]; then\n            MISSING_SPECS=\"${MISSING_SPECS}${MISSING_SPECS:+, }$MODEL_NAME\"\n        fi\n    done\n\n    if [ -n \"$MISSING_SEEDERS\" ] || [ -n \"$MISSING_SPECS\" ]; then\n        echo \"❌ Pre-commit validation failed!\"\n        [ -n \"$MISSING_SEEDERS\" ] && echo \"Missing seeders: $MISSING_SEEDERS\"\n        [ -n \"$MISSING_SPECS\" ] && echo \"Missing specs: $MISSING_SPECS\"\n        echo \"Fix: php artisan make:model:full <Model> --category=development\"\n        echo \"Or skip: git commit --no-verify\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\nfi\n\n# 4. Documentation\necho \"📚 Checking documentation...\"\nif ! php artisan docs:sync --check >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n    echo \"⚠️  Documentation incomplete. Run: php artisan docs:sync --check\"\n    echo \"Skip with: git commit --no-verify\"\n    exit 1\nfi\necho \"✅ Docs OK\"\n\nexit 0","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"e1614d6a-e9c5-4efe-b085-633367ba7d46","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"#!/bin/sh\n#\n# Pre-commit hook: Pint (PHP style), model/seeder and docs checks.\n# Install: cp scripts/pre-commit .git/hooks/pre-commit && chmod +x .git/hooks/pre-commit\n#\n\nset -e\nROOT=\"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\n# 1. Laravel Pint (PHP code style)\necho \"📝 Running Pint...\"\nif ! vendor/bin/pint --test --dirty 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"❌ Pint check failed. Run: vendor/bin/pint --dirty --format agent\"\n    exit 1\nfi\necho \"✅ Pint passed\"\n\n# 3. New models: seeders and specs (exclude Concerns/ traits, Scopes/, and known non-models)\nSTAGED_MODELS=$(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=A | grep -E '^app/Models/.*\\.php$' | grep -v -E '^app/Models/(Concerns|Scopes)/' || true)\nSKIP_NAMES=\"BelongsToOrganization OrganizationScope Categorizable TermsVersion UserTermsAcceptance\"\n\nif [ -n \"$STAGED_MODELS\" ]; then\n    MISSING_SEEDERS=\"\"\n    MISSING_SPECS=\"\"\n    for MODEL_FILE in $STAGED_MODELS; do\n        MODEL_NAME=$(basename \"$MODEL_FILE\" .php)\n        case \" $SKIP_NAMES \" in *\" $MODEL_NAME \"*) continue ;; esac\n        SEEDER_FOUND=false\n        for CATEGORY in essential development production; do\n            if [ -f \"database/seeders/$CATEGORY/${MODEL_NAME}Seeder.php\" ]; then\n                SEEDER_FOUND=true\n                break\n            fi\n        done\n        if [ \"$SEEDER_FOUND\" = false ]; then\n            MISSING_SEEDERS=\"${MISSING_SEEDERS}${MISSING_SEEDERS:+, }$MODEL_NAME\"\n        fi\n        if [ ! -f \"database/seeders/specs/${MODEL_NAME}.json\" ]; then\n            MISSING_SPECS=\"${MISSING_SPECS}${MISSING_SPECS:+, }$MODEL_NAME\"\n        fi\n    done\n\n    if [ -n \"$MISSING_SEEDERS\" ] || [ -n \"$MISSING_SPECS\" ]; then\n        echo \"❌ Pre-commit validation failed!\"\n        [ -n \"$MISSING_SEEDERS\" ] && echo \"Missing seeders: $MISSING_SEEDERS\"\n        [ -n \"$MISSING_SPECS\" ] && echo \"Missing specs: $MISSING_SPECS\"\n        echo \"Fix: php artisan make:model:full <Model> --category=development\"\n        echo \"Or skip: git commit --no-verify\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\nfi\n\n# 4. Documentation\necho \"📚 Checking documentation...\"\nif ! php artisan docs:sync --check >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n    echo \"⚠️  Documentation incomplete. Run: php artisan docs:sync --check\"\n    echo \"Skip with: git commit --no-verify\"\n    exit 1\nfi\necho \"✅ Docs OK\"\n\nexit 0","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019DjpwQPRyBrCvuquBsQSmh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pre-commit hook runs `php artisan docs:sync --check` but uses the system `php` not the specific `php@8.5` binary. Let me check if it passes with the system php or if there's an issue.\n\nActually, looking more carefully: the hook runs `php artisan docs:sync --check >/dev/null 2>&1` — it's using the system `php`, not the php@8.5. If the system php is an older version or a different binary...\n\nWait, maybe it IS the same one and the issue is something else. The hook shows:\n```\n📚 Checking documentation...\n\n\n```\n\nBut we just ran `php artisan docs:sync --check` with the php@8.5 binary and it says \"All items are documented!\". Maybe the hook is running before our new docs file is staged? We did stage it with `git add docs/developer/backend/controllers/dashboardcontroller.md docs/developer/backend/controllers/README.md docs/.manifest.json`, so let me verify what's actually staged.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1060,"cache_read_input_tokens":76219,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1060},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"5a30a3f4-d914-455b-a165-9bb1cda9808c"}
