{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XXyjg8tsRs6UBENXmSNdmy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pre-commit hook uses the system `php` (Herd's PHP 8.4), but the project requires PHP 8.5+. The hook runs `php artisan docs:sync --check` which fails with an exit code that makes the hook think docs are incomplete, but actually the check fails because of the wrong PHP version.\n\nThis is the same Herd php issue we've been dealing with. The pre-commit hook uses the system `php` binary (8.4) which can't even run the artisan command.\n\nThe fix options:\n1. Update the pre-commit hook to use the correct PHP binary - but that would modify the script which is a hook\n\n\n2. Use `--no-verify` to bypass the hook - allowed in this situation since the hook itself is broken (uses wrong PHP version)\n3. Set up Herd to isolate the site to PHP 8.5\n\nThe hook is actually exiting with code 255 from a fatal PHP error, which the hook script interprets as documentation being incomplete rather than recognizing it's a version mismatch issue. Looking at the hook logic, it checks if the artisan command fails and treats any non-zero exit as a docs sync failure.\n\nThe real problem is that the hook runs with PHP 8.4 while the project needs 8.5, which is a pre-existing infrastructure issue. Since the docs check passes with the correct PHP version and the hook failure stems from this broken environment rather than actual code problems, using `--no-verify` is justified here. Though I'm second-guessing myself against the instruction to never skip hooks unless explicitly requested, the CLAUDE.md guidelines about not touching certain files and committing properly are also in tension with this situation.\n\nWait, I'm seeing a critical instruction: \"Never ever commit the code without asking me.\" This directly conflicts with the chief agent's autonomous commit step. I need to flag this conflict and ask the user before proceeding with any commit.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1012,"cache_read_input_tokens":77913,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1012},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"a5e56f5d-c74c-4607-a7c7-5f9db7845fb5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XXyjg8tsRs6UBENXmSNdmy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to stop before committing. Two issues:\n\n1. **Global instruction conflict**: Your `CLAUDE.md` says *\"Never ever commit the code without asking me\"* — which overrides the Chief Agent's autonomous commit step.\n\n2. **Pre-commit hook is broken**: The hook uses `php` (Herd's PHP 8.4) but the project requires PHP 8.5+, so `php artisan docs:sync --check` crashes with a fatal error. The hook interprets the crash as \"docs incomplete\" even though everything is actually fine when run with the correct binary.\n\n**What I've completed:**\n- `npm run build` ✓\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` ✓\n- All files staged and ready to commit\n- PRD updated: US-001 `passes: true`\n- `progress.md` created\n\n**The commit that's ready to go:**\n```\nfeat: US-001 - Tailux CSS design token foundation\n```\n\n**Your options:**\n1. **Approve the commit** — I'll run it with `--no-verify` since the hook fails due to a broken PHP PATH (not a code issue), and the docs check passes when run with `php@8.5`\n2. **Fix Herd site isolation first** — isolate this site to PHP 8.5 via Herd (so the hook uses the right binary), then commit normally\n3. **Commit yourself** — run `git commit --no-verify -m \"feat: US-001 - Tailux CSS design token foundation\"` manually\n\nWhich would you prefer?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1012,"cache_read_input_tokens":77913,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1012},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"13906b18-daff-4720-b7d8-a93a2992ee49","uuid":"f1d52e58-0b85-4f84-8547-70cdfa7c819e"}
