 as a theme variable, it should automatically generate the corresponding `bg-secondary` utility class, so I can use those directly in the CVA compound variants.\n\nWriting the color variants file... Continuing with the style variants for the remaining color options... Finishing the neutral variant definitions...\n\nI'm realizing the PRD specifically calls for CVA definitions covering filled, soft, and outlined variants across those seven semantic colors, so this colorVariants export is on the right track. But I shouldn't bake in base classes like `inline-flex items-center` since different components will have their own layout needs—Button, Badge, and Alert all require different base styling. I'll keep the color variants focused and let each component handle its own structural classes.\n\nNow I'm ready to create both files with this cleaner approach.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1399,"cache_read_input_tokens":71645,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1399},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d67112a8-e0f1-41f5-bf61-d36ba5bdd92e","uuid":"c5278d6f-eeff-4c42-9343-66aa746eaf0b"}
