posed/`\",\n   471→        \"`Foundation/` stories: Colors, Typography, Icons, Tailux Tokens, Theme Presets, Theme Preview\",\n   472→        \"Every component has at least one CSF3 story with `argTypes`, `autodocs`, and realistic mock data\",\n   473→        \"`saas/` stories: each SaaS component with realistic props (e.g. `trial-banner` with `daysRemaining=5`, `feature-gate` in both `hasAccess=true` and `hasAccess=false` states)\",\n   474→        \"`admin/` stories: each admin component with mock data\",\n   475→        \"`shells/` stories: each shell layout shown with placeholder content inside each slot\",\n   476→        \"All stories respect the Storybook theme toolbar (dark/light, palette, radius, skin)\",\n   477→        \"`ThemeCustomizer` story renders with `canCustomize: true` (mocked)\",\n   478→        \"`GlobalSearch` story uses mock search results (no real backend call)\",\n   479→        \"`npm run storybook` runs all stories with 0 errors\"\n   480→      ],\n   481→      \"priority\": 32,\n   482→      \"passes\": false\n   483→    },\n   484→    {\n   485→      \"id\": \"US-033\",\n   486→      \"title\": \"ThemeSettings backend — sidebar layout, font, menu color, menu accent\",\n   487→      \"description\": \"As an admin, I need additional theme dimensions (sidebar layout variant, font choice, menu background color, and menu accent style) stored in the database so the full visual identity of the app can be configured per organization.\",\n   488→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   489→        \"`app/Settings/ThemeSettings.php` extended with 4 new fields: `sidebar_layout` (default: `'main'`, options: `main|sideblock`), `font` (default: `'inter'`, options: `inter|geist|poppins|outfit|plus-jakarta-sans`), `menu_color` (default: `'default'`, options: `default|primary|muted`), `menu_accent` (default: `'subtle'`, options: `subtle|strong|bordered`)\",\n   490→        \"New settings migration in `database/settings/` for the 4 new fields\",\n   491→        \"`php artisan migrate` completes successfully\",\n   492→        \"All 4 fields added to `SettingsOverlayServiceProvider::OVERLAY_MAP` with `orgOverridable: true`\",\n   493→        \"`HandleInertiaRequests` `share()` updated — `theme` key now includes `layout`, `font`, `menuColor`, `menuAccent` alongside existing fields\",\n   494→        \"`theme-from-props.tsx` extended to apply `data-sidebar-layout`, `data-font` (already exists — verify), `data-menu-color`, `data-menu-accent` on `document.documentElement`\",\n   495→        \"`resources/css/themes.css` extended with CSS blocks for each new dimension: `[data-sidebar-layout=\\\"sideblock\\\"]`, `[data-menu-color=\\\"primary|muted\\\"]`, `[data-menu-accent=\\\"strong|bordered\\\"]`\",\n   496→        \"Frontend types updated in `resources/js/types/index.d.ts`\",\n   497→        \"`php artisan settings:cache` completes successfully\",\n   498→        \"`vendor/bin/pint --dirty --format agent` passes\",\n   499→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n   500→      ],\n   501→      \"priority\": 33,\n   502→      \"passes\": false\n   503→    },\n   504→    {\n   505→      \"id\": \"US-034\",\n   506→      \"title\": \"ThemeCustomizer UX — compact panel, Try Random, all dimensions\",\n   507→      \"description\": \"As an admin, I want the ThemeCustomizer panel to match the UX quality of shadcn/ui create — a compact property list where each row shows the current value and expands inline, plus a \\\"Try Random\\\" shuffle button and the ability to export/import the theme as JSON.\",\n   508→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   509→        \"`theme-customizer.tsx` redesigned as a compact vertical list panel (inspired by shadcn/ui create's right panel): each theme dimension is a single row showing `Property Name / Current Value + icon`; clicking a row expands an inline option picker below it; only one row expanded at a time\",\n   510→        \"Panel sections cover all theme dimensions in order: Theme Mode, Preset, Layout, Style/Dark Palette, Primary Color, Base Color/Light Scheme, Font, Menu Color, Menu Accent, Card Skin, Radius\",\n   511→        \"\\\"Try Random\\\" button at the top of the panel (keyboard shortcut `R` while panel is open): randomizes all theme dimensions to a valid random combination and applies them immediately\",\n   512→        \"\\\"Export theme\\\" button: copies the current 9 theme dimensions as a JSON blob to the clipboard; shows \\\"Copied!\\\" toast\",\n   513→        \"\\\"Import theme\\\" action: a small textarea that appears when clicking \\\"Import\\\"; pasting valid theme JSON and clicking \\\"Apply\\\" applies all dimensions at once; invalid JSON shows an inline error\",\n   514→        \"\\\"Reset to defaults\\\" link at the bottom reverts all attributes to system defaults and clears saved org overrides\",\n   515→        \"\\\"Save for Organization\\\" button POSTs all dimensions (including new ones from US-033) to the settings API\",\n   516→        \"All dimension changes still apply immediately via `data-*` attributes on `document.documentElement` (optimistic UI, no page reload)\",\n   517→        \"Hover over a preset card or color swatch shows a live preview instantly (mouse-enter applies the change; mouse-leave reverts to current saved state; click commits the selection)\",\n   518→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n   519→      ],\n   520→      \"priority\": 34,\n   521→      \"passes\": false\n   522→    },\n   523→    {\n   524→      \"id\": \"US-035\",\n   525→      \"title\": \"Hooks library\",\n   526→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a collection of commonly-needed React hooks available in `resources/js/hooks/` so I don't reinvent them in every component.\",\n   527→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   528→        \"`resources/js/hooks/` directory created with an `index.ts` barrel file that re-exports all hooks\",\n   529→        \"`useDebounce\\u003cT\\u003e(value: T, delay: number): T` implemented — returns a debounced version of the value; updates after `delay` ms of no changes\",\n   530→        \"`useLocalStorage\\u003cT\\u003e(key: string, initialValue: T): [T, Setter, () =\\u003e void]` implemented — synced localStorage state; third return value clears the key\",\n   531→        \"`useMediaQuery(query: string): boolean` implemented — reactive to viewport changes\",\n   532→        \"`useIntersectionObserver(ref, options?): IntersectionObserverEntry | null` implemented — triggers when the element enters/exits the viewport\",\n   533→        \"`useClickOutside(ref, handler)` implemented — calls `handler` when a click occurs outside the given ref\",\n   534→        \"`useEventListener(eventName, handler, element?)` implemented — typed `addEventListener`/`removeEventListener` with cleanup\",\n   535→        \"`usePrevious\\u003cT\\u003e(value: T): T | undefined` implemented — returns the previous render's value\",\n   536→        \"`useWindowSize(): { width: number; height: number }` implemented — reactive window dimensions\",\n   537→        \"`useCopyToClipboard(): [boolean, (text: string) =\\u003e void]` implemented — `copied` is `true` for 2 seconds after copying\",\n   538→        \"`useOnline(): boolean` implemented — returns `true` when browser has network access; reactive to `online`/`offline` events\",\n   539→        \"`useToggle(initial?: boolean): [boolean, () =\\u003e void, (v: boolean) =\\u003e void]` implemented — boolean toggle with optional force-set\",\n   540→        \"`useInterval(callback, delay: number | null)` implemented — safe `setInterval` with cleanup; pass `null` to pause\",\n   541→        \"`useReducedMotion` (already created in US-014) moved here and re-exported from `hooks/index.ts`\",\n   542→        \"`useFocusTrap` (already created in US-014) moved here and re-exported from `hooks/index.ts`\",\n   543→        \"`useKeyboardShortcut` (from US-015) re-exported from `hooks/index.ts`\",\n   544→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n   545→      ],\n   546→      \"priority\": 35,\n   547→      \"passes\": false\n   548→    },\n   549→    {\n   550→      \"id\": \"US-036\",\n   551→      \"title\": \"Utilities library, Error Boundary, and Offline banner\",\n   552→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a shared utility function library, a React Error Boundary component with a custom fallback, and an offline detection banner so these foundational patterns don't get reinvented per feature.\",\n   553→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   554→        \"`resources/js/lib/utils/` directory created; new utilities in separate files re-exported from `resources/js/lib/utils/index.ts`; existing `cn()` function in `resources/js/lib/utils.ts` must not be modified or moved\",\n   555→        \"`formatDate(date: Date | string, format?: string): string` implemented — locale-aware; default format is `MMM D, YYYY`; wraps `date-fns`\",\n   556→        \"`formatRelativeTime(date: Date | string): string` implemented — e.g. `\\\"2 hours ago\\\"`, `\\\"just now\\\"`, `\\\"in 3 days\\\"`; uses `date-fns/formatDistanceToNow`\",\n   557→        \"`formatCurrency(amount: number, currency?: string, locale?: string): string` implemented — defaults to USD + user's browser locale\",\n   558→        \"`formatNumber(n: number, options?: Intl.NumberFormatOptions): string` implemented — compact notation: `1200` → `\\\"1.2K\\\"`, `3_400_000` → `\\\"3.4M\\\"`\",\n   559→        \"`formatBytes(bytes: number, decimals?: number): string` implemented — `2_400_000` → `\\\"2.4 MB\\\"`\",\n   560→        \"`truncate(str: string, length: number, suffix?: string): string` implemented — appends `\\\"…\\\"` by default\",\n   561→        \"`slugify(str: string): string` implemented — `\\\"Hello World!\\\"` → `\\\"hello-world\\\"`\",\n   562→        \"`initials(name: string, maxChars?: number): string` implemented — `\\\"John Doe\\\"` → `\\\"JD\\\"`\",\n   563→        \"`groupBy\\u003cT\\u003e(array: T[], key: keyof T): Record\\u003cstring, T[]\\u003e` implemented\",\n   564→        \"`clamp(value: number, min: number, max: number): number` implemented\",\n   565→        \"`randomItem\\u003cT\\u003e(array: T[]): T` implemented — picks a random element\",\n   566→        \"`randomTheme(): ThemeConfig` implemented — picks a random valid combination of all theme dimensions from `tailux-themes.ts` constants\",\n   567→        \"`resources/js/components/ui/error-boundary.tsx` created: class-based React Error Boundary; accepts `fallback` prop (ReactNode or render-prop `(error, reset) =\\u003e ReactNode`); default fallback renders an `ErrorState` component with a \\\"Try again\\\" button that calls `reset()`\",\n   568→        \"`resources/js/components/ui/offline-banner.tsx` created: uses `useOnline()` hook; renders a fixed top banner when offline; auto-dismisses 3 seconds after connection is restored; manual close button available; respects `useReducedMotion`\",\n   569→        \"All utility functions have JSDoc with input/output examples\",\n   570→        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n   571→      ],\n   572→      \"priority\": 36,\n   573→      \"passes\": false\n   574→    }\n   575→  ]\n   576→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n","numLines":581,"startLine":1,"totalLines":581}}}
