{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JdTE2TJzFt3vdS7judUZ1z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `ThemeSettings` has `orgOverridable: true`. The US-004 says the `allow_user_theme_customization` field is NOT orgOverridable. So I can't just add it to `ThemeSettings` without restructuring, since the entire settings class has a single orgOverridable flag.\n\nLooking at the structure, each Settings class has ONE `orgOverridable` flag. Since `ThemeSettings` is already `orgOverridable: true`, and the new field must NOT be orgOverridable, I need to create a new Settings class for this, OR... I could add it to `ThemeSettings` but change the OVERLAY_MAP to separate this field from the orgOverridable group.\n\n\nLet me check how `orgOverridable` actually works by looking at the `orgOverridableKeys()` method and the surrounding code.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":580,"cache_read_input_tokens":61836,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":580},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ed4aaad-a5f8-4391-8e9e-1841360e4b97","uuid":"f2d78def-d903-4b9a-8892-1967a7f1a5a1"}
