eme-customizer.tsx` redesigned as a compact vertical list panel (inspired by shadcn/ui create's right panel): each theme dimension is a single row showing `Property Name / Current Value + icon`; clicking a row expands an inline option picker below it; only one row expanded at a time\",\n        \"Panel sections cover all theme dimensions in order: Theme Mode, Preset, Layout, Style/Dark Palette, Primary Color, Base Color/Light Scheme, Font, Menu Color, Menu Accent, Card Skin, Radius\",\n        \"\\\"Try Random\\\" button at the top of the panel (keyboard shortcut `R` while panel is open): randomizes all theme dimensions to a valid random combination and applies them immediately\",\n        \"\\\"Export theme\\\" button: copies the current 9 theme dimensions as a JSON blob to the clipboard; shows \\\"Copied!\\\" toast\",\n        \"\\\"Import theme\\\" action: a small textarea that appears when clicking \\\"Import\\\"; pasting valid theme JSON and clicking \\\"Apply\\\" applies all dimensions at once; invalid JSON shows an inline error\",\n        \"\\\"Reset to defaults\\\" link at the bottom reverts all attributes to system defaults and clears saved org overrides\",\n        \"\\\"Save for Organization\\\" button POSTs all dimensions (including new ones from US-033) to the settings API\",\n        \"All dimension changes still apply immediately via `data-*` attributes on `document.documentElement` (optimistic UI, no page reload)\",\n        \"Hover over a preset card or color swatch shows a live preview instantly (mouse-enter applies the change; mouse-leave reverts to current saved state; click commits the selection)\",\n        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 34,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-035\",\n      \"title\": \"Hooks library\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a collection of commonly-needed React hooks available in `resources/js/hooks/` so I don't reinvent them in every component.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"`resources/js/hooks/` directory created with an `index.ts` barrel file that re-exports all hooks\",\n        \"`useDebounce\\u003cT\\u003e(value: T, delay: number): T` implemented — returns a debounced version of the value; updates after `delay` ms of no changes\",\n        \"`useLocalStorage\\u003cT\\u003e(key: string, initialValue: T): [T, Setter, () =\\u003e void]` implemented — synced localStorage state; third return value clears the key\",\n        \"`useMediaQuery(query: string): boolean` implemented — reactive to viewport changes\",\n        \"`useIntersectionObserver(ref, options?): IntersectionObserverEntry | null` implemented — triggers when the element enters/exits the viewport\",\n        \"`useClickOutside(ref, handler)` implemented — calls `handler` when a click occurs outside the given ref\",\n        \"`useEventListener(eventName, handler, element?)` implemented — typed `addEventListener`/`removeEventListener` with cleanup\",\n        \"`usePrevious\\u003cT\\u003e(value: T): T | undefined` implemented — returns the previous render's value\",\n        \"`useWindowSize(): { width: number; height: number }` implemented — reactive window dimensions\",\n        \"`useCopyToClipboard(): [boolean, (text: string) =\\u003e void]` implemented — `copied` is `true` for 2 seconds after copying\",\n        \"`useOnline(): boolean` implemented — returns `true` when browser has network access; reactive to `online`/`offline` events\",\n        \"`useToggle(initial?: boolean): [boolean, () =\\u003e void, (v: boolean) =\\u003e void]` implemented — boolean toggle with optional force-set\",\n        \"`useInterval(callback, delay: number | null)` implemented — safe `setInterval` with cleanup; pass `null` to pause\",\n        \"`useReducedMotion` (already created in US-014) moved here and re-exported from `hooks/index.ts`\",\n        \"`useFocusTrap` (already created in US-014) moved here and re-exported from `hooks/index.ts`\",\n        \"`useKeyboardShortcut` (from US-015) re-exported from `hooks/index.ts`\",\n        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 35,\n      \"passes\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-036\",\n      \"title\": \"Utilities library, Error Boundary, and Offline banner\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a shared utility function library, a React Error Boundary component with a custom fallback, and an offline detection banner so these foundational patterns don't get reinvented per feature.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"`resources/js/lib/utils/` directory created; new utilities in separate files re-exported from `resources/js/lib/utils/index.ts`; existing `cn()` function in `resources/js/lib/utils.ts` must not be modified or moved\",\n        \"`formatDate(date: Date | string, format?: string): string` implemented — locale-aware; default format is `MMM D, YYYY`; wraps `date-fns`\",\n        \"`formatRelativeTime(date: Date | string): string` implemented — e.g. `\\\"2 hours ago\\\"`, `\\\"just now\\\"`, `\\\"in 3 days\\\"`; uses `date-fns/formatDistanceToNow`\",\n        \"`formatCurrency(amount: number, currency?: string, locale?: string): string` implemented — defaults to USD + user's browser locale\",\n        \"`formatNumber(n: number, options?: Intl.NumberFormatOptions): string` implemented — compact notation: `1200` → `\\\"1.2K\\\"`, `3_400_000` → `\\\"3.4M\\\"`\",\n        \"`formatBytes(bytes: number, decimals?: number): string` implemented — `2_400_000` → `\\\"2.4 MB\\\"`\",\n        \"`truncate(str: string, length: number, suffix?: string): string` implemented — appends `\\\"…\\\"` by default\",\n        \"`slugify(str: string): string` implemented — `\\\"Hello World!\\\"` → `\\\"hello-world\\\"`\",\n        \"`initials(name: string, maxChars?: number): string` implemented — `\\\"John Doe\\\"` → `\\\"JD\\\"`\",\n        \"`groupBy\\u003cT\\u003e(array: T[], key: keyof T): Record\\u003cstring, T[]\\u003e` implemented\",\n        \"`clamp(value: number, min: number, max: number): number` implemented\",\n        \"`randomItem\\u003cT\\u003e(array: T[]): T` implemented — picks a random element\",\n        \"`randomTheme(): ThemeConfig` implemented — picks a random valid combination of all theme dimensions from `tailux-themes.ts` constants\",\n        \"`resources/js/components/ui/error-boundary.tsx` created: class-based React Error Boundary; accepts `fallback` prop (ReactNode or render-prop `(error, reset) =\\u003e ReactNode`); default fallback renders an `ErrorState` component with a \\\"Try again\\\" button that calls `reset()`\",\n        \"`resources/js/components/ui/offline-banner.tsx` created: uses `useOnline()` hook; renders a fixed top banner when offline; auto-dismisses 3 seconds after connection is restored; manual close button available; respects `useReducedMotion`\",\n        \"All utility functions have JSDoc with input/output examples\",\n        \"`npx tsc --noEmit` passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 36,\n      \"passes\": false\n    }\n  ]\n}","numLines":576,"startLine":1,"totalLines":576}}}
